{"key":"post-12142651","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12142651</id>\n<content>Straw should be shredded and then soaked for 2 to 24 hours before pasteurizing.&amp;nbsp; If you're soaking in warm soapy water, you can go for the minimum 2 hour soak.&amp;nbsp; If not, and using cold water, let it soak for 24 hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;After soaking, an easy method is to simply heat the water the straw is soaking in to the desired temp and then maintain it.&amp;nbsp; I doubt seriously that pouring 160F water over wet, cold straw is going to maintain the proper temp for 90 minutes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12143727</next>\n<prev>12142631</prev>\n<first>12141932</first>\n<last>12168429</last>\n<when>1267739795</when>\n<utime>03/04/10 11:56 PM</utime>\n</post>"}